## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f6e5-197">Uma pesquisa assíncrona pode mostrar resultados conforme forem encontradas durante a pesquisa simultaneamente por resultados adicionais.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f6e5-197">An asynchronous search can show results as they are found while simultaneously searching for additional results.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3f6e5-198">Isso é útil para tarefas como preencher caixas de listagem.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f6e5-198">This is useful for tasks such as populating list boxes.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f6e5-199">A configuração padrão dessa propriedade é `false`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f6e5-199">The default setting for this property is `false`.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f6e5-200">O exemplo c# a seguir mostra como criar uma pesquisa assíncrona.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f6e5-200">The following C# example shows how to create an asynchronous search.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
// Bind to the users container.  
DirectoryEntry entry = new DirectoryEntry("LDAP://CN=users,DC=fabrikam,DC=com");  
// Create a DirectorySearcher object.  
DirectorySearcher mySearcher = new DirectorySearcher(entry);  
//Set the Asynchronous property to true.  
src.Asynchronous = true;  
//Use the FindAll method to get search results.  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
